headline: Qualcomm wraps up $2.4bn acquisition of Alphawave Semi
summary: Alphawave Semi develops high-speed connectivity and compute technologies including IP, custom silicon, products and chiplets to improve data transfer efficiency.

headline: Inside Intel’s new Arizona fab, where the chipmaker’s fate hangs in the balance
summary: At Intel’s new fab in Arizona, 18A is in high-volume production. With no major outside customers and a 10% government stake, is it enough to save the chipmaker?

headline: Can Intel’s New Arizona Chip Fab Bring It Back From The Brink?
summary: Intel is now in high-volume production of its latest chip node, 18A, at a new Arizona fab it hopes will compete with TSMC. But so far, no major external customers are making on 18A. Following years of missteps, Intel faces an uphill battle to regain customer trust. In the meantime, its received billions from Nvidia, SoftBank and the U.S. government - which took a 10% stake in the company. CNBC got the first ever on-camera tour inside Fab52 and asked its foundry head why this time, it won’t fail.
